I'm looking to take this class next semester as well. I've heard from friends it is a 3 unit class in terms of workload, but 4 unit class in terms of concepts (if that makes sense, probably not). However, one additional benefit of INFO 159 is that it will count as the "6 upper division units outside your department" required for L&S CS students, so what better way to spend those units by learning something cool like NLP vs. some other heavy reading/heavy essay humanities courses.
